.TH save-all 3
.XI save-all - "Save all modified files (with query)"
.SH NAME
save-all \- Save all modified files (with query)
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.I n
.B save-all
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBsave-all\fR  cycles through all buffers,  dictionaries,  registry files and
current  session  writing back any changes made. For each buffer,  dictionary,
session or registry  file which has been modified the user is prompted  before
the changes are saved, a value of \fBy\fR  initiates  the save, \fBn\fR  skips
the save.
.PP
The  argument  \fIn\fR  can  be  used  to  change  the  default  behavior  of
save-all described above, \fIn\fR is a bit based flag where:-
.IP \fB0x01\fR
Enables the user prompt before the file is saved  (default). If this flag is
not supplied then all modified files will automatically be written.
.SH NOTES
\fBsave-all\fR is a macro defined in \fCme.emf\fR, using commands
.Ht save-some-buffers 2 ,
.Ht save-dictionary 2 ,
.Ht save-session 3 ,
and
.Ht save-registry 2 .
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
